enByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Mike Blake/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Tesla has sold car and batteries to SpaceX, and the two companies are jointly working on chips and software.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>The Do’s and Don’ts of Buying Used Tech Gadgets</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/technology/personaltech/used-tech-refurbished.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/technology/personaltech/used-tech-refurbished.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/technology/personaltech/used-tech-refurbished.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>With a shortage of some components driving up costs of consumer electronics, refurbished devices are an attractive alternative to buying new.</description><dc:creator>Brian X. Chen</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 09:03:49 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">E Commerce</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Price</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">iPhone</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Laptop</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electronics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Amazon</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Facebook</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Service Content</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/05/business/03techfix/03techfix-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Sisi Yu</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>How to Remove Apps You Never Use (or at Least Hide Them)</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-app-removal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-app-removal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-app-removal.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>If you need space back on your phone or tablet, removing built-in and unused apps can help free up storage and reduce screen clutter.</description><dc:creator>J. D. Biersdorfer</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 09:02:01 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Smartphone</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tablet computer</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">None</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Android</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Samsung</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mobile Apps</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Service Content</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/10/technology/personaltech/10BIZ-TECHTIP-TOP/10BIZ-TECHTIP-TOP-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Apple</media:credit><media:description>In the Storage settings, Apple’s iOS software for iPad and iPhone shows how much of the device’s storage is being used and offers several ways to reclaim space.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>What to Know About Planned Social Media Bans in Australia, the U.K. and Beyond</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/15/world/europe/social-media-bans-worldwide.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/15/world/europe/social-media-bans-worldwide.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/15/world/europe/social-media-bans-worldwide.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Britain said it would ban social media access for children under 16 starting in 2027, joining several other countries introducing similar measures.</description><dc:creator>Amelia Nierenberg</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 11:19:17 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Children</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Parenting</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Motherhood</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Fatherhood</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Australia</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Britain</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/15/multimedia/15int-social-media-bans-wtk-HFO-top-qzwg/15int-social-media-bans-wtk-HFO-top-qzwg-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Katie Collins/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Students in Wimbledon, London, during an interview this year about social media. Public opinion in many countries has coalesced around the idea that more must be done to protect children online.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Should You Outsource Your Morning Routine to a Chatbot?</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/04/magazine/ai-chatbot-morning-routine-videos.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>A.I. wants to help you start the day. Its suggestions? Drink coffee and get dressed.</description><dc:creator>Sophie Haigney</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2026 09:03:39 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Habits and Routines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">TikTok</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/14/magazine/14mag-screenland/14mag-screenland-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Aniyah Uniquee/@Aniyahuniquee</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>Riding High After I.P.O., SpaceX Will Buy A.I. Start-Up for $60 Billion</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/business/spacex-cursor-aquisition-ipo.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/business/spacex-cursor-aquisition-ipo.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/business/spacex-cursor-aquisition-ipo.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>SpaceX exercised its option to acquire Cursor in an all-stock deal, bolstering Elon Musk’s ambitions in artificial intelligence.</description><dc:creator>Ryan Mac and Gregory Schmidt</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 12:41:38 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SpaceX</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cursor</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mergers and Acquisitions</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anysphere</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/16/multimedia/16Biz-SpaceX-Cursor-zhlf/16Biz-SpaceX-Cursor-zhlf-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Jordan Vonderhaar for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>The deal to acquire Cursor signals how Elon Musk is delving further into A.I. and expanding SpaceX from its main businesses of building rocket ships and offering satellite internet service.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Why Waymo’s Driverless Taxis Won’t Be on Your Streets Anytime Soon</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/technology/waymo-driverless-taxis-politics.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/technology/waymo-driverless-taxis-politics.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/technology/waymo-driverless-taxis-politics.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The Silicon Valley company’s ambitions to roll out autonomous cars nationwide have hit political roadblocks in some of the country’s biggest markets.</description><dc:creator>David McCabe</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 14:13:42 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Car Service</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Driverless Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Self-Driving Cars</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Taxis</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Waymo</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">District of Columbia Council</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Kathleen Hochul</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Zohran Mamdani</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Teamsters</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/04/30/multimedia/WAYMO-politics-02-pvqz/WAYMO-politics-02-pvqz-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Manuel Orbegozo for The New York Times</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>D.O.J. Seeks to Halt Pollution Lawsuit Against Elon Musk’s Data Center</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/climate/xai-musk-mississippi-grok-turbine-lawsuit-naacp.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/climate/xai-musk-mississippi-grok-turbine-lawsuit-naacp.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/climate/xai-musk-mississippi-grok-turbine-lawsuit-naacp.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The department cited national security concerns, saying Elon Musk’s company had played a crucial role in the Iran war. It also argued it has the authority to stop environmental lawsuits brought by citizens.</description><dc:creator>Karen Zraick and Hiroko Tabuchi</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 17:27:45 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">x.ai</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Air pollution</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federal Courts</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Justice Department</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Clear Air Act</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">NAACP</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mississippi</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Federalism</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/16/multimedia/16cli-musk-doj-vjqt/16cli-musk-doj-vjqt-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Brad J. Vest for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Construction at xAI’s power plant in Southaven, Miss., in February. The NAACP has sued the company over air pollution from generators there.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>A.I. Boom Ignites Asian Chip Companies</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/technology/taiwan-south-korea-ai-chips.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/technology/taiwan-south-korea-ai-chips.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/technology/taiwan-south-korea-ai-chips.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>They make much of the gear that goes into giant data centers. Demand for their products is shifting the balance of tech power.</description><dc:creator>Paul Mozur and Tripp Mickle</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 09:00:52 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer Chip</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Hynix Semiconductor</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">NVIDIA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SK Group</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Samsung</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jen-Hsun Huang</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Jensen Huang</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">China</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">South Korea</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Taiwan</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Supply Chain</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/05/multimedia/00-Data-Center-Boom-01-vktl/00-Data-Center-Boom-01-vktl-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>I-Hwa Cheng/Agence France-Presse — Getty Images</media:credit><media:description>Nvidia’s chief executive, Jensen Huang, signing a Taiwanese bank note at the Computex technology conference in Taipei, Taiwan, this month.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>The Cloud Has Sound: The Unrelenting and Unseen Cost of A.I. Data Centers</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/us/data-centers-noise-pollution.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/us/data-centers-noise-pollution.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/17/us/data-centers-noise-pollution.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>As tech giants rush to build infrastructure, some residents who live near data centers say a constant low-frequency vibration is ruining their health and homes.</description><dc:creator>Adeel Hassan</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 09:00:27 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Noise</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Zoning</category><category domain="http://www.nytim